    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Chole Bhature is a classic North Indian dish featuring spicy chickpeas (chole) served with deep-fried bread (bhature). It's a hearty and flavorful meal enjoyed by all age groups.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>45 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <h5>For Chole:</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup chickpeas (soaked overnight)</li>
        <li>2 onions (chopped)</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes (pureed)</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>
        <li>1 tsp chole masala</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>2 tbsp oil</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>For Bhature:</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>2 cups all-purpose flour (maida)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup curd (yogurt)</li>
        <li>1/4 tsp baking soda</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp salt</li>
        <li>Water as needed</li>
        <li>Oil for deep frying</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Pressure cook soaked chickpeas with salt until soft.</li>
        <li>Heat oil, add cumin, then saut√© onions till golden. Add ginger-garlic paste and cook.</li>
        <li>Add tomato puree and spices. Cook till oil separates.</li>
        <li>Add boiled chickpeas. Simmer for 15 minutes. Adjust seasoning.</li>
        <li>For Bhature, mix flour, curd, soda, and salt. Knead to a soft dough. Rest for 2 hours.</li>
        <li>Divide dough, roll into rounds and deep fry till puffed and golden.</li>
        <li>Serve hot chole with fluffy bhature, onions, and pickle.</li>
    </ol>
